President Barack Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation to attend the Opening Ceremony of the 2016 Paralympic Summer Games in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. The delegation will attend athletic events, meet with U.S. athletes, and attend the Opening Ceremony. The Honorable Sylvia Burwell, Secretary of Health and Human Services, will lead the delegation. Other members of the delegation include the U.S. Ambassador to Brazil, Liliana Ayalde, Claudia L. Gordon from the Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs, William Reynolds III, a retired U.S. Army Captain and U.S. Team Captain for the Invictus Games 2016, and Bonnie St. John, a one-time Paralympic silver medalist and two-time Paralympic bronze medalist in women's skiing.